    <text id="B0257T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Garnett informs Jordan that he will pay H. Holland the money he is owed for work
                    with the railroad company.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Office <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> Central <abbr expan="Railroad">R. R.</abbr> Company,
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. J. Jordan<lb/><unclear>Ag</unclear> Bureau <orig reg="etc">&amp;c</orig><lb/>Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-04-25">April 25 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Mr. John H. Richardson will pay you fourteen <hi rend="underline">08</hi>/100
                    dollars <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> due by the <abbr expan="Virginia">V<hi
                            rend="super">a</hi></abbr> Central <abbr expan="Railroad">RailRd</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Company">Co.</abbr> to H. Holland for work in the month of
                    September 1867, as appears by the payroll.</p>

                <p>I find that the <abbr expan="amount">am<hi rend="underline">t</hi></abbr> which
                    was due to H. Holland for work done in August 1867 = five 36/100 dollars was
                    paid to H <unclear>Giles</unclear>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> to the payroll for that month &amp; the
                    <unclear>work</unclear> of H Holland to Giles filed therewith.</p>

                <p>I will thank you to receipt the <orig reg="endorsed">indorsed</orig> order for
                    the sum herewith sent &amp; return it to me by Mr. Richardson</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully <orig reg="etc">&amp;c</orig></salute>
                    <signed>J. Garnett, Jr.</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">[on seperate sheet]VIRGINIA CENTRAL RAILROAD.<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> J. H. Richardson will please pay to J
                        Jordan <abbr expan="Agent">Agt</abbr> Bureau at Staunton the $14 08 due H
                        Holland &amp; take his receipt therefor in the enclosed order &amp;
                        bring it to me on his return. I enclose the money to pay
                    him.<lb/>[signed]JG</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
